{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyNnaJFCpYzdiqk655svf/SZ"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)"],"metadata":{"id":"UYoGiBQ_pN0d"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Object-Oriented Programming in Python is a way of organizing code using classes and objects to make it more modular, reusable, and easy to maintain."],"metadata":{"id":"JMhWD0tOpTNU"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##Class - Blueprint to create objects\n","\n","\n","- A class is a blueprint or template that defines what kind of data and methods an object will have.\n","\n","- It does not create anything in memory until we create an object."],"metadata":{"id":"VMQOp9qYqBFX"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##Object / Instance-Instance created from class stored in memory/Same as object\n","\n","- An object (or instance) is a real entity(Something that actually exists in memory and can be used) created from a class.\n","- When we create an object, Python allocates memory and stores the data inside it.\n","\n","d1 = Dog(\"Rocky\")\n","\n","\n","Here, d1 is a reference pointing to the object in memory.\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"iWbCShRfqPCy"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Class → just a design (nothing real yet)\n","\n","Object (Instance) → real thing created from that design\n","\n","```text\n","Example in coding\n","class Dog:\n","    pass\n","\n","👉 This is NOT a real entity\n","✔ Just a blueprint\n","❌ No memory allocated yet"],"metadata":{"id":"BmdkB-b2tg5T"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","d1 = Dog()\n","\n","👉 Now:\n","✔ Object is created\n","✔ Memory is allocated\n","\n","👉 This d1 object is a real entity"],"metadata":{"id":"2IjbU5k3t3Of"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###What is an Object Internally\n","\n","\n","In Python, everything is an object.\n","\n","a = 10 → creates an integer object\n","\n","d1 = Dog() → creates a class object\n","\n","Variables are just references pointing to objects in memory."],"metadata":{"id":"YTAnzDc6qyxi"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###How Object Creation Works\n","\n","When we create an object:\n","\n","1. Memory is allocated in heap\n","2. __init__() is automatically called\n","3. Object data is initialized\n","4. Reference is returned"],"metadata":{"id":"mrQOrtSBq8kf"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##init() Method- Initializes object automatically\n","\n","- __init__() is a constructor-like method that runs automatically when an object is created.\n","- It is used to initialize the object’s data, not to create the object."],"metadata":{"id":"Z1DHNLnKrMeA"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## self Keyword -Refers to current object\n","\n","- self refers to the current instance of the class.\n","- It is used to access instance variables and methods."],"metadata":{"id":"DSjfZNGZrTpu"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Types of Variables\n","\n","- Instance variables → unique for each object\n","- Class variables → shared across all objects"],"metadata":{"id":"QU8c6xPGrgt2"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["for reference-https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python/python-oops-concepts/"],"metadata":{"id":"9ITTVPZvvJZC"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Four Pillars of OOP\n","\n","- Inheritance → reuse properties from another class\n","- Polymorphism → same method, different behavior\n","- Encapsulation → bind data and methods together\n","- Abstraction → hide internal details"],"metadata":{"id":"l_E8b9furyd5"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Note\n","\n","####Memory Understanding\n","\n","- Objects are stored in heap memory, and variables act as references pointing to them.\n","- Each object has its own separate memory."],"metadata":{"id":"NTnKcL7sr9ZH"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#\n","a class defines the structure, and objects are created in memory as instances of that class, where data is initialized using init, and variables act as references to those objects."],"metadata":{"id":"jRGs4L-IsS5U"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"EzrgiDuMlOrK","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775931726866,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"e84f0fcd-baed-4354-db0d-8ee1acb40428"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Rocky\n","3\n","Canine\n"]}],"source":["class Dog:\n","  species = \"Canine\" # class attribute\n","\n","  def __init__(self, name, age):\n","    self.name = name # Instance attribute\n","    self.age = age # Instance attribute\n","\n","#creating object of the Dog class\n","d1 = Dog(\"Rocky\", 3)\n","\n","print(d1.name)\n","print(d1.age)\n","print(d1.species)"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Dog:\n","    def __init__(self, name):\n","        self.name = name\n","\n","d1 = Dog(\"Rocky\")\n","print(d1)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"2pV2pPxgw7Aj","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775932261158,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":11,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"e2bd0b19-47d6-4461-e25f-f1198223ad4c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["<__main__.Dog object at 0x7c9241a33650>\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##__str__()\n","\n","- __str__() tells Python:\n","\n","- “When someone prints my object, show THIS instead"],"metadata":{"id":"BLfwJUlx0O8g"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Dog:\n","  def __init__(self,name):\n","    self.name=name\n","\n","  def __str__(self):\n","    #return self.name  # what to show\n","    return f\"This dog name is {self.name}.\"\n","\n","d1=Dog(\"Rocky\")\n","print(d1)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7oUE1EjJ0UzP","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775932521348,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":8,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"0c5852a5-d6f4-4e7f-e6f0-bcfcda9f93ca"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["This dog name is Rocky.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["####What actually happens internally\n","\n","```text\n","When you do:\n","\n","print(d1)\n","\n","Python automatically does:\n","\n","d1.__str__()\n","\n","👉 Whatever you return → gets printed\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"Zrl4ADmM1GBn"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["- Without __str__() → Python prints memory address\n","\n","- With __str__() → You control the output\n","\n","- __str__() is used to control how an object looks when printed"],"metadata":{"id":"hK963xHU1fiu"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Polymorphism - many forms"],"metadata":{"id":"Kxf1XE0Y1vUf"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Same method name → different behavior based on object/data"],"metadata":{"id":"IsEGaJcKNnwl"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Polymorphism is an OOP concept where the same method name can behave differently depending on the object or input.\n","\n","```text\n","Remote control\n","\n","You press “Power” button:\n","\n","TV → turns ON\n","AC → turns ON\n","Fan → turns ON\n","\n","👉 Same action → different behavior\n","👉 That is polymorphism"],"metadata":{"id":"6_SnPvR7NrFs"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","Payment system 💳\n","\n","Same method: pay()\n","\n","CreditCard → deduct from bank\n","UPI → pay via app\n","Wallet → deduct wallet balance\n","\n","👉 Same method → different implementations"],"metadata":{"id":"1S8InMTFOABR"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","Animal sound 🐶🐱\n","\n","Same method: sound()\n","\n","Dog → Bark\n","Cat → Meow\n","Cow → Moo"],"metadata":{"id":"-K1urjiaOFCm"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 3. Types of Polymorphism\n","\n","1. Compile-time Polymorphism\n","- Happens before execution\n","- Achieved by Method Overloading\n","2. Runtime Polymorphism\n","- Happens during execution\n","- Achieved by Method Overriding"],"metadata":{"id":"F46GftxYOK_s"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###1. Method Overloading (Compile-time idea)\n","- Definition- Same method name, different parameters--default arguments, args, kwargs\n","\n","Python does NOT support true overloading like Java/C++"],"metadata":{"id":"hffsWf4OOXWZ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Example using default arguments\n","\n","class Calculator:\n","  def add(self, a,b, c=0):\n","    return a+b+c\n","\n","obj=Calculator()\n","\n","print(obj.add(3,4))\n","print(obj.add(3,4,5))"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"heKNN2IKN1pB","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775939415751,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":10,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"4eec53ff-74c4-453a-f713-5b4fa979d3ea"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["7\n","12\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Example using *args\n","class Demo:\n","    def show(self, *args):\n","        print(args)\n","\n","d = Demo()\n","d.show(1)\n","d.show(1, 2)\n","d.show(1, 2, 3)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"sSQo2gsEPPop","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775939441944,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":46,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"d38a38a2-98d4-4569-92ab-3cffb8eecc51"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["(1,)\n","(1, 2)\n","(1, 2, 3)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Overloading = same method, different inputs**"],"metadata":{"id":"cD8J-KOGPaFE"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["####5. Method Overriding (Runtime polymorphism)\n","- Definition-Child class gives a new implementation for parent method"],"metadata":{"id":"czGGgeFWPfID"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Animal():\n","  def sound(self):\n","    print(\"Animal makes sound\")\n","\n","class Dog(Animal):\n","  def sound(self):\n","    print(\"Dog Bark\")\n","\n","class Cat(Animal):\n","  def sound(self):\n","    print(\"Cat Meow\")"],"metadata":{"id":"XKZhgWAJPRs7"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["a1=Dog()\n","a2=Cat()\n","\n","a1.sound()\n","a2.sound()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"gVr4cTnNPQfK","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775939659238,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"dc70ec83-d2da-40a4-cb81-1fc8d4be14be"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Dog Bark\n","Cat Meow\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Why runtime?**\n","\n","Because Python decides while running:\n","\n","- if object = Dog → Bark\n","- if object = Cat → Meow"],"metadata":{"id":"dAjazmokQP0U"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Python decides method based on:**\n","\n","- OBJECT TYPE (at runtime)\n","\n","- NOT method name"],"metadata":{"id":"myMmZVXMQcNH"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","obj.method()\n","   ↓\n","Check object type\n","   ↓\n","Search method in that class\n","   ↓\n","If not found → go to parent"],"metadata":{"id":"Zp4l5QDmQlwr"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["print(Dog.__mro__)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"I6qHICC_QrRB","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775939796671,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":51,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"1da7b619-dfff-4015-e1a2-540387ff1c9d"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["(<class '__main__.Dog'>, <class '__main__.Animal'>, <class 'object'>)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def make_sound(Animal):\n","    Animal.sound()\n","\n","make_sound(Dog())\n","make_sound(Cat())\n","\n","#Output changes based on object → runtime polymorphism"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"jWJBqa3zQ4-j","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775939864748,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":10,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"09912149-203b-48e9-d915-9826132dcd1c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Dog Bark\n","Cat Meow\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Payment:\n","    def pay(self):\n","        print(\"Processing payment\")\n","\n","class UPI(Payment):\n","    def pay(self):\n","        print(\"Paying using UPI\")\n","\n","class Card(Payment):\n","    def pay(self):\n","        print(\"Paying using Card\")\n","\n","def process(payment):\n","    payment.pay()\n","\n","process(UPI())\n","process(Card())"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"SxOx21K8RIyF","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775939917610,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":41,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"4265ec22-dd51-48bd-c6e6-952f6bde7aa3"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Paying using UPI\n","Paying using Card\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## MRO (Method Resolution Order)\n","MRO (Method Resolution Order)is the order in which Python searches for a method or attribute.\n","\n","When we create an object and call a method:\n","\n","- Python first checks in the object’s class\n","- If the method is not found, it moves to the parent class\n","- Then continues to higher-level classes\n","- Finally, it checks the object class (built-in base class)\n","```text\n","So the order is:\n","\n","Child → Parent → object"],"metadata":{"id":"bvidDWYXSsMl"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Parent:\n","    def show(self):\n","        print(\"Parent method\")\n","\n","class Child(Parent):\n","    pass   # No show() here\n","\n","c = Child()\n","c.show()\n","\n","#Child → Parent → object"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"I9Q65Ya3UGFY","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775940692952,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":46,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"398ca4b8-b208-4838-c4f6-52e83ca80d6c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Parent method\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##super() = go to next class in MRO"],"metadata":{"id":"pkbr53YXTAoV"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Parent:\n","    def show(self):\n","        print(\"Parent\")\n","\n","class Child(Parent):\n","    def show(self):\n","        super().show()\n","        print(\"Child\")"],"metadata":{"id":"wmB4mrCNTDZ_"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#(Child, Parent, object)"],"metadata":{"id":"GDsyWTqCTGgX"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["c = Child()\n","c.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"9_TpIRIMTKPO","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775940447719,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":15,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"3d2deb03-d691-4a72-cc4f-279110921b79"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Parent\n","Child\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","Step-by-step:\n","1.Python finds show() in Child\n","2.Runs Child.show()\n","3.Inside it → super().show()\n","4.Moves to next in MRO → Parent\n","5.Executes Parent.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"2r5VIHfSTV85"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class A:\n","    def show(self):\n","        print(\"A\")\n","\n","class B(A):\n","    def show(self):\n","        print(\"B\")\n","\n","class C(B):\n","    def show(self):\n","        super().show()\n","        print(\"C\")"],"metadata":{"id":"0Mgx-h34Ti9R"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["C().show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Zdztbsh-Tm2N","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775940570486,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":48,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"cf6e447d-1650-436f-a4b4-5bfbd58179f2"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["B\n","C\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["B().show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"wp8Zho-NTrbI","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775940594449,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":40,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"e11ba737-f2a9-4fd3-9b13-5cc1ad203c1e"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["B\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["MRO (Method Resolution Order) defines the order in which Python searches for methods in a class hierarchy. When a method is called, Python first checks the object’s class, then moves to parent classes, and finally to the **base object class**. The super() function is used to call the next method in the MRO, allowing us to access parent class behavior in a controlled way.\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"BsAcFxTET5_X"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**base object class**.--in mro (child- parent- object)\n","Built-in functions like print() and str() internally call special methods such as __str__(). If these methods are not defined in a class, Python uses the default implementation provided by the base object class through MRO."],"metadata":{"id":"U00K1iHLZBRm"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Inheritance\n","\n","one class can use properties and methods of another class.\n","\n","A child class gets features from a parent class."],"metadata":{"id":"NjdsOQ0Oas1h"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Animal:\n","  def __init__(self, name):\n","    self.name=name\n","\n","  def info(self):\n","    print(\"animal name: \", self.name)\n","\n","class Dog(Animal):\n","  def sound(self):\n","    print(self.name,\"Barks\")\n","\n","d=Dog(\"Rocky\")\n","d.info()\n","d.sound()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"oJ2LZt2cZCE-","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775942797881,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":43,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"e017e8fe-defb-426a-991b-4b4aacdcb89c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["animal name:  Rocky\n","Rocky Barks\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","What is happening here?\n","Animal is the parent/base class\n","Dog is the child/derived class\n","Dog automatically gets name and info() from Animal\n","Dog also has its own method sound()\n","\n","So inheritance helps with:\n","\n","code reuse\n","less repeated code\n","easy maintenance\n","real-world relationships like Animal -> Dog"],"metadata":{"id":"DZO5ep6xcdUm"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### super()\n","\n","super() is used in child class to call parent class methods, especially __init__()."],"metadata":{"id":"6NgT27Z0ckrI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Animal:\n","  def __init__(self,name):\n","    self.name=name\n","\n","class Dog(Animal):\n","  def __init__(self,name,breed):\n","    super().__init__(name)\n","    self.breed=breed\n","\n","  def details(self):\n","    print(self.name,self.breed)\n","\n","d=Dog(\"Buddy\",\"Golden Retriever\")\n","d.details()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"O8TEIF9Zcehb","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775943194740,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":9,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"32e8ae4c-08d5-43f7-9158-e56c97511f0c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Buddy Golden Retriever\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Person:\n","    def speak(self):\n","        print(\"Person can speak\")\n","\n","class Student(Person):\n","    def study(self):\n","        print(\"Student can study\")\n","\n","s = Student()\n","s.speak()\n","s.study()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"rxwnIv_2dy6j","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775943235400,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":21,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"7410d8e2-fc7a-4898-8334-6cc2686b3d77"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Person can speak\n","Student can study\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Data Abstraction\n","\n","Abstraction means showing only important things and hiding internal details.\n","\n","```text\n","example\n","\n","Think of:\n","\n","ATM machine 💳\n","You:\n","insert card\n","enter PIN\n","withdraw money\n","\n","❌ You don’t know how bank system works internally\n","\n","✔️ That is abstraction"],"metadata":{"id":"uqGnzy2heAJY"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n","\n","class Shape(ABC):   # Abstract class\n","\n","    @abstractmethod\n","    def area(self):\n","        pass"],"metadata":{"id":"_O-zQcAKeDqM"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Rectangle(Shape):\n","    def __init__(self, w, h):\n","        self.w = w\n","        self.h = h\n","\n","    def area(self):\n","        return self.w * self.h"],"metadata":{"id":"6giGIW_5eZLv"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["r = Rectangle(5, 10)\n","print(r.area())"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"eEfhZix1ea_Y","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775943400020,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"1c10a771-10c8-4465-dfa4-fd0fcf99ddaf"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["50\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","What is happening here?\n","Shape → abstract class (blueprint)\n","area() → method defined but no logic\n","Rectangle → provides actual implementation\n","\n","👉 User only calls:\n","\n","r.area()\n","\n","❌ Doesn’t care how it is calculated\n","✔️ Only cares about result"],"metadata":{"id":"puDITE4vfEDM"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["```text\n","Key Terms\n","\n","1. Abstract Class\n","Blueprint for other classes\n","Cannot create object directly\n","Used using ABC module\n","\n","2. Abstract Method\n","Method with no implementation\n","Child class must implement it\n","@abstractmethod\n","def area(self):\n","    pass\n","\n","🔹 Why Abstraction?\n","\n","✔️ Hides complexity\n","✔️ Makes code simple\n","✔️ Improves security\n","✔️ Easy to maintain & reuse\n","\n","\n","\n","👉 Abstraction = Hide + Show\n","\n","Hide → logic\n","Show → result"],"metadata":{"id":"MEmTDeQHfgNG"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","class Car:\n","    def start(self):\n","        print(\"Car started\")\n","\n","c = Car()\n","c.start()\n","\n","\"\"\" You just call start()\n","You don’t know engine process\n","\n","That is abstraction\"\"\""],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":71},"id":"qsV3462TfuSy","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775943765373,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":13,"user":{"displayName":"Mounika Bopperla","userId":"10007237717483354690"}},"outputId":"7141df03-add6-4e58-8919-9c978d5d2a71"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Car started\n"]},{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["' You just call start()\\nYou don’t know engine process\\n\\nThat is abstraction'"],"application/vnd.google.colaboratory.intrinsic+json":{"type":"string"}},"metadata":{},"execution_count":27}]}]}